<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFEB6A55FA599B561F50BF73" blockId="16.[1444,2650,3343,3502]" lastBlockId="17.[106,1320,741,3497]" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="775" pageId="16" pageNumber="774">
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFEB6A54FA599B56140EB665" pageId="16" pageNumber="774" type="reference_group">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFEB6A54FA599B561841B602" bold="true" box="[1445,1601,3343,3376]" pageId="16" pageNumber="774">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFEB6A54F9AD9B561688B602" authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1840" box="[1617,2184,3343,3376]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="774" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hesperida">Vespertilio hesperida [sic] Temminck, 1840</taxonomicName>
, “Les bords de la Mer rouge vers les cotés d’Abyssinie [= the shores of the Red Sea toward the coast of 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFEB6A54F68F9B6F17F2B665" box="[2419,2546,3382,3415]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="16" pageNumber="774">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
].”
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFEB6A55FA5B9B041F50BF73" lastPageId="17" lastPageNumber="775" pageId="16" pageNumber="774" type="discussion">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFEB6A54FA5B9B0418C0B64C" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1447,1728,3421,3454]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="774" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hesperidus">Pipistrellus hesperidus</taxonomicName>
has generally been considered a synonym of P. kuhliz; however, it is now recognized as a distinct species because of its morphological and genetic distinctions. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFEA6A55FC72976C1AA5BA64" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[910,1189,309,342]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="775" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hesperidus">Pipistrellus hesperidus</taxonomicName>
seems to be sister to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFEA6A55FC8097051A00BA4F" baseAuthorityName="Tomes" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[892,1024,348,381]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="775" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rusticus">P. rusticus</taxonomicName>
based on limited genetic data and chromosomal similarities. Exact distributional limits between P. /esperidus and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFEA6A55FC82978F1DEBBAC1" baseAuthorityName="Kuhl" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[894,1003,470,499]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="775" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuhlii">P. kuhlii</taxonomicName>
are uncertain. Canary Islands populations might represent either species and are tentatively included under 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFEA6A55FCC094111DE2B95B" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[828,994,584,617]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="775" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hesperidus">P. hesperidus</taxonomicName>
here. There is considerable variation in morphology across the current distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFEA6A55FBD194CE1AD6B98A" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[1069,1238,663,696]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="775" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hesperidus">P. hesperidus</taxonomicName>
. Subspecies recognized here almost certainly represent distinct species based on genetic and karyological grounds; however, not all populations have been tested, making it difficult to assign them to a species. West African populations mightalso represent a fourth distinct taxon based on high genetic distance and distinct karyotype from southern African populations. There is also considerable divergence between Madagascan and mainland populations, indicating that 
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFEA6A55FF8F95F31F19B8F9" box="[115,281,938,971]" name="Madagascar" pageId="17" pageNumber="775">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
specimens also represent a distinct species, for which the name humbloti might be available (the name was recently allocated to 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFEA6A55FC8A958B1A18B8C1" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[886,1048,978,1011]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="775" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hesperidus">P. hesperidus</taxonomicName>
based on examination of syntypes for the name). Distributions of subspecies are estimates. Three subspecies recognized.
</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
